column1: Topic title: Pakatan hopes to win only 50 seats next election

column8: text

https://sg.news.yahoo.com/pakatan-hopes-att...-005900860.htmlPakatan hopes to attain 50 parliamentary seats in GE14[U]JOHOR BARU: Pakatan Harapan has unveiled a shortlist of 50 parliamentary seats it hopes to win in the 14th general election (GE14).PKR vice-president Rafizi Ramli said the seats include 15 in Johor, namely Johor Baru, Pasir Gudang, Tebrau, Sembrong, Tanjung Piai, Labis, Segamat, Sekijang, Pulai and Sri Gading."Some of these seats were won by Barisan Nasional with a small majority of votes in GE13," he told the media after launching the ‘Jom Bina Semula Negara’ campaign here yesterday.The two-month campaign at 22 locations nationwide will focus on issues such as the minimum wage and the Goods and Services Tax (GST). -- BERNAMAThey know that they can't defeat the glorious BN!
